text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia latzii, also known as Latz's wattle and Tjilpi wattle) is a shrub of the genus Acacia (in the family Fabaceae and the subgenus Plurinerves). It is native to the Finke bioregion (in the south of the Northern Territory and the north of South Australia).
